    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-02-01T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-02-01T00:00:00-05:00" n="308"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d308">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00119 Control (Germany)/2–145: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Acting Secretary of State</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_GJC1" type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Grew</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Malta</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-02-01">1 February
                            1945</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p rend="flushleft">Nr: <gloss target="#t_CRICKET1">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Cricket</hi>
                    </gloss> 45</p>
                <p>For Acting Secretary of State <hi rend="italic">Only</hi> from Secretary
                        <persName corresp="#p_SERJ1">Stettinius</persName>.</p>
                <p>Have dispatched the following to <persName corresp="#p_WJG1">Winant</persName>
                    after conference which <persName corresp="#p_EA1">Eden</persName> and I had with
                    General <persName corresp="#p_M4">Marshall</persName> and Field Marshal
                        <persName corresp="#p_B10">Sir Alan Brooke</persName>.</p>
                <quote rend="blockquote">
                    <p>“You are Authorized immediately to inform the European Advisory Commission of
                        this government’s approval of the protocol on zones of occupation for
                        Germany. <persName corresp="#p_EA1">Eden</persName> is likewise telegraphing
                        the British Government’s approval.”</p>
                </quote>
                <p>Please advise <persName corresp="#p_MJJ1">McCloy</persName>.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
